The paper deals with face grouping, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The use of deep learning approaches and imitation learning (a type of machine learning) suggests that the paper may also belong to sub-categories such as machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and robotics (cs.RO). Additionally, the paper discusses the need for manual correction of erroneous grouping, which suggests a potential application in human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
